getImpressionsUseActivities

public boolean getImpressionsUseActivities()
Returns whether or not impressions will be displayed in a separate activity (true), or in a view at the front of the host activity (false).

setImpressionsUseActivities

public void setImpressionsUseActivities(boolean impressionsUseActivities)
Set whether or not to launch interstitials and the More Apps page in their own activity. This is required for Chartboost to work with a NativeActivity. It may also be a more optimal solution for certain engines, such as Unity. Please use care, as the onPause-onStop/onStart-onResume cycle will be called for the originating activity when showing and hiding the impressions. If false (default behavior), impressions will be displayed in a view above the other content views in your host activity.

setIdentityTrackingDisabledOnThisDevice

getForcedOrientationDifference

public CBOrientation.Difference getForcedOrientationDifference()
The angular difference between the actual orientation of the device and the orientation at which impressions will be displayed. Normally this would be 0, but overriding via setOrientation(CBOrientation) may change this.

Returns:
a CBOrientation#Difference object representing the angle difference
